SIMPLE: worldling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worldling
<hw>World"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[<ets>World</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <def>A person whose soul is set upon gaining
temporal possessions; one devoted to this world and its
enjoyments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A foutre for the world and <qex>worldlings</qex> base.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If we consider the expectations of futurity, the
<qex>worldling</qex> gives up the argument.</q>
<rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>worldlings</qex> blot the temple's gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worldly</ent>⟦br⟧
